-- S&P lowers Uganda sovereign credit rating to B from B+
-- By Thuy Ong
-- Fri Jan 17, 2014 01:11AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Jan 17 (Reuters) - Credit ratings agency Standard & Poor's on Friday downgraded  Uganda's sovereign credit rating to B from B+, with a stable outlook.

S&P also affirmed its 'B' short-term and local currency sovereign credit ratings. The downgrade reflects S&P's view that Uganda's fiscal position has weakened relative to previous forecasts.